node.text: Visited “The Wall That Heals” this evening. This is a 3/4 scale replica of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial in Washington DC that travels around the country and stopped in my town this weekend. A sobering and poignant visit for me. Although this wasn’t my war, I can certainly appreciate their sacrifice. Enjoyed trading stories with the other veterans in attendance though. Military service is kind of like a family I guess. It spans generations and has its own unique bond. I wouldn’t trade that for anything. To all that served, welcome home. To those we’ve lost, may you never be forgotten. #thewallthatheals #vietnamveteransmemorial #vietnamwarmemorial #vietnamwar #usarmy #usmc #usaf #usnavy #uscg
Absolutely a family and like no other! 😉💞 Thank you!  And such a moving photo. Beautiful.
My father in law did the freedom flight and it was quite an amazing experience for him!❤ #thankstoallwho serve
@katcooper1127 thank you! Yeah, apparently there’s a couple that travel around.
Excellent capture 👏👏👏 I visited the national memorial when I was in college in DC ~ such a reverent place. I had no idea there was a traveling exhibition.
It was in my town a couple of years ago.  My dad never, ever, talked about Vietnam. I can't imagine what it was like.

🇺🇸🙏 always remember and be thankful to those who served. I am very thankful to the USA that they fought the good fight back then and ended the threat of Communism which in the end freed so many people around the world from foul tyranny! I am thankful that the US was and still is there in the world to help the little guy against a deranged neighbour or there to stop threats to whatever semblence of stability there is in our world.
My respects! 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸
Great image, and a great thing to visit and witness. It set up down here in Ripley County a few years ago.🇺🇸
